"title": "7364: fellowship offering",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7364",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Sacrificial meals shared by offerer, people and priests. The name of these offerings is related to the Hebrew “shalom”, meaning “wholeness” or “peace”, and they are therefore also known as “peace offerings”.</p>\n<h2>Fellowship offerings were required by God</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:24\">EXO 20:24</a></p>\n<h3>Their purpose was thanksgiving, vow fulfilment or freewill offering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11-Lev7:18\">LEV 7:11–7:18</a></p>\n<h2>Regulations for making a fellowship offering</h2>\n<h3>The animal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1\">LEV 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:6\">LEV 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:12\">LEV 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Its slaughter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:2\">LEV 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:8\">LEV 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:13\">LEV 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:5-Lev17:6\">LEV 17:5–17:6</a></p>\n<h3>All requirements must be fulfilled for the offering to be acceptable</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:5\">LEV 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:21\">LEV 22:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:29\">JOS 22:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:22\">AMO 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:24\">AMO 5:24</a></p>\n<h2>The fellowship offering was shared</h2>\n<h3>God received the best</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:3-Lev3:5\">LEV 3:3–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:9-Lev3:11\">LEV 3:9–3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:14-Lev3:16\">LEV 3:14–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>The priests received their share as food</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:29-Lev7:34\">LEV 7:29–7:34</a></p>\n<h3>The people ate the rest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:14\">LEV 10:14</a></p>\n<h2>Fellowship offerings affirmed the covenant relationship</h2>\n<p>The Sinai covenant with Israel:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:24\">EXO 20:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4-Exod24:6\">EXO 24:4–24:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:31-Josh8:32\">JOS 8:31–8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:8\">1SA 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:25\">1KI 9:25</a></p>\n<h2>The celebration of fellowship offerings</h2>\n<h3>At seasonal festivals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:19\">LEV 23:19</a> <em>the Feast of Weeks</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:39\">NUM 29:39</a> <em>the Feast of Tabernacles</em></p>\n<h3>On other religious and national occasions</h3>\n<p>At the completion of the time of separation of a Nazirite:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:14\">NUM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:17-Num6:18\">NUM 6:17–6:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:10\">NUM 10:10</a> <em>at New Moons and other festivals</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:17\">NUM 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:23\">NUM 7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:29\">NUM 7:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:8\">NUM 15:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:7\">DEU 27:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:17-2Sam6:18\">2SA 6:17–6:18</a> <em>on bringing the ark to Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:25\">2SA 24:25</a> <em>on locating the site for the temple</em>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:63-1Kgs8:64\">1KI 8:63–8:64</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:7\">2CH 7:7</a> <em>at the dedication of the temple</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:35\">2CH 29:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:22\">2CH 30:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:2\">2CH 31:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:16\">2CH 33:16</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:14\">PRO 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:15\">EZK 45:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:17\">EZK 45:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:2\">EZK 46:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:12\">EZK 46:12</a></p>\n<h2>Fellowship offerings in idolatrous worship</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:6\">EXO 32:6</a></p>",
